Jason and the rest of the staff are really sweet. They play a great variety of music from old school hip hop to 80s pop. Cool little patio tiki bar in the back along with free parking lot.

Always a great place to drink cheap and dance your butt off on their dance floor.

I came here one night and tried to order a burger. The server told me no, I couldn't have one. I didn't know what to say, and then he paused and said that I could order one in 5 minutes. Why? I asked. He told me that burgers were half price on Wednesday evenings starting at 7 p.m. and he wanted me to get the best deal. I had a good laugh, and called him back soon after to order my half price burger. 5/5 excellent service and tasty burger.

This is one of the greatest places in Bethesda, a hidden treat. Great people, great bartenders, and it can be as frugal as you can contain yourself. Believe me, it might be hard. A good menu, especially after a beer or two, or whatever you like, and they serve late, which is cool. It's not five star, it's friendly. Bring a smile! A lot of cooks and servers and late night workers hang after their hours. The regulars will ask you your story. Pool tables, first come first served. The outside bar is always rockin' and the music is almost always on, unless you want to catch a game or something and they'll put it on. I heartily recommend you check it out.
